-- Shares of Hong Kong's PCCW suspended -HKEx
-- By Denny Thomas
-- Sun Jan 12, 2014 10:23PM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Jan 13 (Reuters) - Trading in the shares of Hong Kong telecommunications company PCCW Ltd <0008.HK>, controlled by tycoon Richard Li, was suspended on Monday, according to Hong Kong Exchange.

Trading in the shares of another PCCW group company, Pacific Century Premium Developments Ltd <0432.HK>, was also halted from after the stock's price surged about 15 percent. PCCW owns about 74.5 percent of Pacific Century Premium.